Hello
So this is no longer the way to define validParams. This templated way has been fully deprecated.
For all your objects that are defining their parameters this way, you should transition them to this syntax:
Header
class <ClassName>: public <BaseClass>
{
public:
  static InputParameters validParams();
...


Source in .C file
InputParameters
<ClassName>::validParams()
{
  InputParameters params = <BaseClass>::validParams();
  params.addClassDescription("Imposes the essential boundary condition $u=g$, where $g$ "
                             "is calculated by a function.");
  params.addParam<FunctionName>("function", 0, "The function describing the Dirichlet condition");
  return params;
}

